`recreate_angular_velocity.py` (+ `filter_tune.yaml`) in each `oddjob_vibeAnalysis_*` dir recreates
PX4's `vehicle_angular_velocity` (both `xyz` gyro and `xyz_derivative` dgyro) from raw
`sensor_gyro_fifo`, then re-filters with YAML-set `IMU_GYRO_CUTOFF / IMU_DGYRO_CUTOFF /
IMU_GYRO_NF0/NF1_FRQ/BW` to tune offline. It reuses `analyze_imu_vibration.py`'s
`fifo_to_series`/`direct_fft`/`save_fig` via `sys.path.insert`. Run:
`python3 recreate_angular_velocity.py LOG.ulg --config filter_tune.yaml` â†’ plots+metrics in
`recreate_av_<stem>_plots/`. Plots are in **deg/s** and copy `analyze_imu_vibration`'s FFT style
(linear axes 0..Nyquist, flat-top PSD, reusing `aiv.annotate_top_peaks` + `aiv.add_lpf_lines`); the
PSD compares recreated-vs-logged (not raw â€” raw's 99 Hz peak is ~250x larger and blows a linear-y
axis; raw lives in their `imu_fft_gyro_*.png`). See [[oddjob-vibe-psd-summary]] for the PSD CSV tooling.

