Non-obvious facts (verified on OD1A079_nexus_endurance.ulg):
- Controller gyro = `sensor_selection.gyro_device_id` = **3670026** = `sensor_gyro_fifo` **multi_id=0**,
  **8000 Hz** (dt=125 Âµs). This is the FIFO that feeds `vehicle_angular_velocity` â€” **not** 6684714
  (the 2 kHz device the PSD CSVs analyze). Params: CUTOFF=25, DGYRO=30, NF0/NF1 disabled, DNF_EN=0
  (dynamic notch off), SENS_BOARD_ROT=24 (=ROTATION_PITCH_90), SENS_BOARD_Y_OFF=âˆ’4Â°, gyro=CAL_GYRO1.
- **FIFO logging-dropout gotcha**: the SD log drops chunks of the 8 kHz FIFO (124 dropouts, ~195k
  samples on OD1A079). The FC had continuous data â†’ smooth logged output; filtering across the
  reconstructed gaps **rings**, which looks like a 4% mismatch. Excluding Â±0.1 s around each gap
  (keeps ~98%) â†’ **gyro NRMSE â‰ˆ 0.1%, dgyro â‰ˆ 1%, corr 0.99999** (validated). The tool does this
  automatically and shades dropouts on the time-series plots.
- The **25 Hz gyro LPF crushes the ~99.4 Hz vibration** in `vehicle_angular_velocity` (~âˆ’48 dB), so
